    RECEIVE_WOUND(L)          LOCAL FUNCTIONS           RECEIVE_WOUND(L)
 
    NAME
        receive_wound() - causing permanent damages to the various 
	    living status of the current object.
 
    SYNOPSIS
        varargs int receive_wound(string type, int damage, object who)
 
    DESCRIPTION
	this function is defined in /feature/damage.c, and inherited by
	all living objects. it is used to deduct damage points from the
	current living object's permanent value of different status. 
	
	type is a string containing the types of the damage, valid types
	are gin, kee and sen. and the result is set within the eff_gin,
	eff_kee and eff_sen property of the object.

	damage is a positive integer indicating how much damage of that
	type will be deducted from the living.

	who is an object, indicating who causes this damage, if any. the
	last_damage_from property of the current object will be set
	accordingly.

	the return value of this function is damage.

    SEE ALSO
	receive_damage(), receive_heal(), receive_curing()

